glass recycling austin, recycle austin, plastic recycling austin, commercial recycling austin, austin waste management, URO','If you have questions about glass recycling in Austin or aluminum recycling in Dallas, Balcones Resources is here to help. See your City of Austin recycling schedule today.','Balcones Resources | City of Austin Recycling Schedule, Aluminum Recycling Dallas, Glass Recycling Austin',1),(16,'SingleCycle#REG#','single-cycle','','none','internal-green','','25',120,0,'3','','<div>Our SingleCycle#REG# program was designed for maximum participation. SingleCycle#REG# eliminates the need to separate your recyclables into different containers. Throw all of your recycling in a single bin, and we do the rest.</div><div><br></div><div>Go ahead and throw your soda can in with your paper. Mix your water bottle with your envelopes and sticky notes. No more sorting, no more second guessing, just easy recycling. Your mixed recyclables will arrive at our facility, and we\\\'ll sort them into their proper categories.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>Simply put, you throw it in, we sort it out.</div><div><br></div><div>Let us help alleviate your separation anxiety.&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http://http://www.balconesresources.com/contact-us/contact-us\\\" title=\\\"Contact us\\\" target=\\\"\\\">Contact</a> us to streamline your recycling.</div><div><br></div>','<br>','<br>','<br>','<br>','<br>','<br>','<br>','<br>','<br>','The Cure for Separation Anxiety#TM#','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','',0,'commercial recycling austin, commercial recycling dallas, single stream recycling austin, plastic recycling dallas, electronics recycling dallas, computer recycling dallas, glass recycling austin, cardboard recycling austin, boxboard recycling austin, balconesresources.com','Balcones Resources specializes in single stream recycling in Austin with advancements in both Austin and Dallas commercial recycling.','Balcones Resources | Commercial Recycling Austin, Single Stream Recycling Austin, Commercial Recycling Dallas',1),(17,'Accepted Materials','accepted-materials','','none','internal-green','','26',190,0,'3','','<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"></span><p>Below is a list of what is accepted in the <b>City of Austin\'s</b> residential single-stream recycling service. Please reference this list and remember to recycle right! <img src=\"/rsrc/client-uploads/23536329178354.jpg\" height=\"650\" width=\"488\"></p><p><font size=\"2\">*To download a copy of the City of Austin\'s \"Recycle Right\" poster go here:&nbsp;<a target=\"\" title=\"City of Austin Recycle Right Poster\" href=\"http://www.keyetv.com/images/RecycleRightPoster_Events1.pdf\"> http://www.keyetv.com/images/RecycleRightPoster_Events1.pdf</a></font><br></p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Paper</span><br>Newspaper, office paper, junk mail, envelopes, wrapping paper<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Boxboard and cardboard</span><br>Corrugated cardboard and boxboard including:<br><ul><li>\r\nCereal boxes</li><li>Shoe boxes</li><li>Most gift boxes</li><li>Soda/beverage containers</li><li>Most food packaging containers such as boxes of macaroni and cheese, rice and microwave meals</li></ul><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"><br></span><strong>Aluminum and metal cans<br></strong>Food cans (labels left on OK),\r\n soda cans, clean aluminum baking tins (free of food residue), clean \r\naluminum trays, pie plates (free of food reside) clean, balled aluminum \r\nfoil (2 inches or larger)<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Glass</span><br>Jars and bottles<br><br><b>&#8232;Plastic containers</b> <br># 1 through # 7, including yogurt and margarine tubs&#8232;','<ul><li>Plastic bags&#8232;</li><li>Styrofoam (cups, egg cartons, take-out \r\ncontainers)&#8232;</li><li>Pizza boxes from take-out or delivery services&#8232;</li><li>Yard \r\nwaste/leaves (set out for yard trimmings pick up)&#8232;</li><li>Food waste&#8232;</li><li>Garbage \r\n(you may be charged for extra garbage if you put garbage in your \r\nrecycling cart)</li><li>&#8232;Helium tank&#8232;s</li><li>Large metal items such as frying pans and \r\nmetal pipes</li><li>&#8232;Large plastic items (plastics that are gallon-sized or \r\nsmaller are ok)</li><li>&#8232;Wire coat hangers (recycle at your local dry cleaners)</li></ul>','For more information about the City of Austin’s recycling program, please go to <a target=\"_blank\" title=\"\" href=\"http://www.austinrecycles.com/\">www.austinrecycles.com</a>.<br><br>For information about a specific item, please visit the City of Austin\'s itemized, online A to Z guide to recycling, reusing, composting and more at <a target=\"_blank\" title=\"What do I do with?\" href=\"http://www.austintexas.gov/what-do-i-do\">www.austintexas.gov/what-do-i-do</a>.<br>','<br>','<br>','<br>','<br>','<br>','<br>','<br>','Recycle Right','What cannot be recycled in the cart?','City of Austin Resources','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','',0,'aluminum recycling austin, cardboard recycling austin, glass recycling austin, paper recycling austin, austin waste management, single stream recycling austin, city of austin recycle, city of austin recycling','Balcones Resources accepts a number of recyclable materials including Paper recycling, cardboard recycling and glass recycling in Austin, TX.','Balcones Resources | Paper Recycling Austin, Cardboard Recycling Austin, Glass Recycling Austin',1),(19,'Our Story','our-story','','none','internal-blue','','30',500,0,'2','','We started as a recycling company. It seems like an obvious statement, but it is what separates us from our competition. We were not founded as a side business to compliment garbage hauling. We subsist purely on our ability to recover resources and divert them from the landfill. <br><br><iframe src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/GZM0cp4kVD8\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"268\" width=\"476\"></iframe><br><br>Kerry and Becky Getter founded Balcones Resources in 1994 in Austin, Texas. In the mid-\'90s the only commodity being actively recycled in a commercial setting was white paper, and the Balcones team saw the need to change the way Texas recycled. “We had an opportunity to make an impact both environmentally and economically,” remarked Kerry. Balcones introduced the Anything that Tears#TM# program, which simplified office recycling and allowed property managers to quickly quantify their efforts through monthly environmental reports and a reduction of costs related to landfill hauling fees.<br><br>Kerry remembers, “It was a challenge at first because we really had to get into the trenches and educate everyone involved in an organization. The janitorial crews were very important because we needed to move the material efficiently and effectively throughout the buildings, and their buy-in was crucial to the success of the program. Education became a necessary component, and we started to see the fruits of our labor in the form of increased participation and a reduction in waste from the different locations we serviced.”<br><br>Fast-forward 18 years, and we have facilities in Austin, Dallas and Little Rock and have grown to become one of the top 50 recyclers in North America. We service approximately 75% of Austin’s Class A office buildings and 80% of the Class A buildings in downtown Dallas. In addition to multi-tenant facilities, Balcones is also the chosen recycling partner for several corporate campuses, manufacturing facilities and distribution centers with major customers such as the University of Texas at Austin, the Capitol Complex, Seton Hospital System, Pepsico, JCPenney and the Clinton Library, just to name a few.<br><br>Our new state-of-the-art facility in Austin is a testament to our innovation. The $25 million facility has the ability to process 25 tons per hour. It is equipped with technology that increases our efficiency and allows us to handle new materials. Staying true to our green roots, the facility has several environmentally friendly features including passive lighting, electric car charging station and solar panels.<br><br>Kerry concludes, “We started as paper recyclers, but we’ve transformed into a full service environmental company that works with our customers to reach zero waste goals, streamline waste, educate employees, achieve LEED#REG# certification, or simply take the first step towards a new recycling program.” <br>','<br>','<br>','<br>','<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"></span><br>','<br>','<br>','<br>','<br>','<br>','What a Long, Strange Trip','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','',0,'boxboard recycling austin, electronics recycling dallas, commercial recycling austin, commercial recycling dallas, dallas waste management, austin waste management, plastic recycling dallas, recycle electronics dallas, aluminum recycling dallas, URO, plastic recycling little rock, cardboard recycling little rock, recycling center little rock, recycling little rock','Balcones Resources provides a wide array of recycling services such as electronic recycling in Dallas, glass recycling in Austin, and plastic recycling in Little Rock.&nbsp;','Balcones Resources | Boxboard Recycling Austin, Electronics Recycling Dallas, City of Little Rock Recycling',1),(20,'News/Events','news-and-events','','news','news','','31',600,0,'2','','<br>','<br>','<br>','<br>','<br>','<br>','<br>','<br>','<br>','<br>','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','',0,'recycling schedule austin, dallas waste management, austin waste management, URO Workshops, URO Austin, commercial recycling dallas, commercial recycling austin, aluminum recycling dallas, aluminum recycling austin, single stream recycling austin','News and Events from Balcones Resources including updates to the recycling schedule in Austin, upcoming URO workshops and Austin event recycling info.','Balcones Resources | Recycling Schedule Austin, Event Recycling Austin, URO Works