INSERT INTO `people` VALUES (1,'Sara','Koeninger','Senior VP, Corporate Services','Not one of the best, the best.<br>','Sara has been with Balcones Resources since 1995 and has held a number of positions including sales, marketing and operations. Tasked with a variety of high profile projects, Sara’s impact on Balcones’ footprint is significant.<br><br>Sara was the sole project manager for Balcones Resources’ new MRF in Austin, Texas opened in 2012. From the initial real estate transaction and due diligence, to equipment design and planning, building construction, equipment installation, Sara managed the $25 million dollar project and helped open the facility on-time and on-budget. This state of the art facility was constructed with several green building features and is recognized as one of the finest recycling facilities in the country. <br><br>As Senior Vice President for Balcones Resources’ corporate services, Sara is responsible for a variety of functions within the company.&nbsp; She sits on the Executive Leadership committee, manages the company’s safety program over all three sites, and oversees equipment installation and start-up for Balcones’ customers. <br><br>Sara has a BFA from Southern Methodist University and an MS in Environmental Planning from the University of Texas - School of Architecture. She is a 5th generation Texan and is actively involved with the Hill Country Conservancy.&nbsp; When she isn’t pouring over architectural plans or equipment specifications, she enjoys the company of her dog, Zofie, who often accompanies her to the office.<br>','','leadership-sara-koeninger.jpg','','','208-705-8so5','jack@70kft.com',1,4),(2,'Rusty','Getter','Chief Operating Officer','<br>','<div>Rusty is an old man in recycling years and there isn’t a job he hasn’t performed. Rusty started in 1979 at the Dallas recycling company founded by his father, Richard Getter. Having performed every job within the company, Rusty is all too familiar with every link in the recycling chain.</div><div>As head of the Balcones Resources Commodities Group, Rusty coordinates the incoming recyclable material with the end-user demand for fiber and pulp products, developing relationships with paper mills around the world. He has successfully positioned Balcones Resources as the top provider of high-quality paper-making products – earning the company a reputation as innovators in an otherwise traditional marketplace.</div><div>Rusty is a frequent speaker at industry events such as the Paper Recycling Conference and the Southeast Paper Recycling Conference.</div><div>Rusty is a University of Texas graduate with a BA in Radio-TV-Film and played baseball for The Longhorns. Rusty is married to Gina, and has three daughters and one ugly dog. Rusty began his recycling career after being fired by the Cincinnati Reds for being an imposter.</div>','','leadership-rusty-getter.jpg','','','','',1,2),(3,'Kerry','R. Getter','Chief Executive Officer','<br>','Kerry Getter founded Balcones Resources, Inc. in 1994 with a small group of investors and a focus on commercial recycling in Austin, Texas. Since its inception, Balcones has grown to include additional facilities in Dallas and Little Rock, generating annual revenue of $30,000,000 with 140 total employees. Balcones has developed a diverse revenue model with business units dedicated to commercial and residential recycling, document destruction, the manufacturing of alternative fuels, and environmental consulting.<br><br>Prior to founding Balcones, Kerry was an executive officer for an East Texas Bank Holding Company and pitcher in the Texas Rangers baseball organization. Kerry attended the University of Pennsylvania and graduated from Texas Wesleyan University in Ft. Worth with a BA in Political Science. Kerry is a two time finalist for Ernst &amp; Young’s entrepreneur of the year and serves on the advisory board of the Lady Bird Johnson Wildflower Center at the University of Texas.<br><br>Kerry enjoys fly-fishing, wildlife habitat restoration, and observing migratory waterfowl. Kerry is married to the former Rebecca Shands of Lufkin. He and Becky have two children, Annie Brown and Richie Getter, and three grandchildren who live in Austin.<br>','','leadership-kerry-getter.jpg','','','','',1,1),(4,'Adam','Vehik','Chief Financial Officer','<br>','<div>Adam joined the Balcones Resources team in February 2011, and he was quickly thrown into the fray as the Company was in the middle of negotiations with the City of Austin for their residential material. Though his tenure with Balcones is in its early stages, after his participation in the City negotiations and the funding and construction of the new Austin facility, he feels like a seasoned Balcones vet.</div><div>Adam serves as Chief Financial Officer for Balcones and is responsible for financial statement preparation and analysis, improvement of profitability, coordinating tax and audit work, compliance, capital investments and keeping the company’s bank happy. He is able to handle all of this through the assistance of his all-star team of accountants and controllers.</div><div>Adam’s role isn’t limited to spreadsheets and financial statements. One of his favorite parts of his job is that he engages directly with the different managers to help them work more effectively and efficiently. His ability to gather copious amounts of information and translate it into usable and tangible tools has helped transform the way Balcones conducts business.</div><div>Adam holds a BA in Economics from Vanderbilt University and a JD/MBA from the University of Arkansas. When he isn’t number crunching, Adam enjoys Austin’s outdoor and music scenes and is a supporter of the Hill Country Conservancy. Adam lives in Austin with his wife, Mica and their dog, Zoe.</div>','','leadership-adam-vehik.jpg','','','','',1,3),(5,'Profile','Five','Title 5','<br>','<br>','','User.gif','','','','',0,5),(6,'Profile','Six','Title 6','<br>','<br>','','User.gif','','','','',0,6),(7,'Profile','Seven','Title 7','<br>','<br>','','User.gif','','','','',0,7),(8,'Profile','Eight','Title 8','<br>','<br>','','User.gif','','','','',0,8),(9,'Profile','Nine','Title 9','<br>','<br>','','User.gif','','','','',0,9);
